President Donald J. Trump has issued nominations and appointments for several key administration posts. The nominations include Joseph Ryan Gruters of Florida to be a Member of the Amtrak Board of Directors, William R. Evanina of Pennsylvania to be Director of the National Counterintelligence and Security Center, and John E. Whitley of Virginia to be an Assistant Secretary of the Army (Financial Management & Comptroller). Additionally, President Trump has announced his intent to nominate individuals for the Board of Directors of the Metropolitan Washington Airports Authority and to appoint individuals to the Foreign Claims Settlement Commission, Department of Justice.